news.title: Show law that illegal building can be ratified: Bombay HC
news.para: Chief Justice Dipankar Datta and Justice Madhav Jamdar heard two intervention applications by three residents of Diamond Park wing C and two residents of Farida Mansion to dismiss the PIL that referred to 9 buildings on private land constructed without sanction.

news.title: Chhattisgarh HC stays NRDA move to allot rehabilitation scheme plot to others
news.para: The bench of justice Arvind Singh Chandel directed the NRDA that the plot allotted to the petitioners may not be allotted to any other person till the next date of hearing. The judge granted four weeks’ time to the respondents to submit their reply.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body conducts lottery for MIG plots allocation
news.para: VMRDA chairperson A Vijaya Nirmala said that chief minister YS Jagan Mohan Reddy launched the programme to provide housing sites to the middle-income groups at affordable prices.

news.title: Chennai development body moots higher floor space index near water bodies
news.para: Currently, construction is permitted only 15 metres from water bodies and acquifer recharge areas, with a maximum FSI of 0.8.

news.title: Registered sale deeds can't be unilaterally cancelled: Madras HC
news.para: The bench was passing the order while hearing a batch of petitions referred to it to answer as to 'whether the registrar has the power to accept the deed of cancellation to nullify the deed of conveyance made earlier, when the deed of conveyance has already been acted upon by the transferee.'

news.title: Realty developers continue to expand malls' portfolio on robust demand
news.para: “The retail real estate sector has reached a new level of maturity where smaller sized and lower grade developments are giving way to grade A malls. The existing grade A malls have over 95% occupancy, which is indicative of the demand for quality real estate in this segment,” said Shishir Baijal, CMD, Knight Frank India.

news.title: Building projects with 20,000 sq meter built-up area must have TNPCB consent to operate
news.para: Even construction projects with built-up area less than 20,000 sqm, if they are provided with sewage treatment plant should also get consent of the board for effective monitoring of operation of such plants, the statement said.

news.title: Court reserves orders on bail petitions of Mantri Developers' promoter, son
news.para: ​​The father and son were produced before court through video conference from Central Prison (Parappana Agrahara). Their counsel applied for interim bail, while the public prosecutor moved a petition seeking 10-day police custody.

news.title: Mixed-use land scheme to be launched soon in Greater Noida
news.para: Land marked for mixed-use purposes have plots for residential, institutional, industrial, commercial and recreational purposes – all within the specified area.

news.title: Uttarakhand HC stops builder from constructing motorable road in reserved forest
news.para: The PIL added that rather than a pedestrian path, the builder started constructing a motorable road. The petitioner also alleged that the forest area falls under the Naina Devi Bird Conservation Centre.

news.title: Delhi: Committee likely to submit report on property tax rates by October 10
news.para: The committee initiated hearings on Friday and will continue with the exercise till September 22. So far, a majority of RWAs/market associations have raised objections over the recommended increase in unit area value and occupancy factors in all categories of colonies.

news.title: Draft of revised master plan for Mangaluru to be ready in two months
news.para: Muda commissioner N Bhaskar told TOI that the authority has been working on the revised plan as per the guidelines of Atal Mission for Rejuvenation and Urban Transformation (AMRUT) scheme.

news.title: IT companies, residential enclaves among 15 on SWDs: Bengaluru civic body
news.para: These structures are built on more than 104 survey numbers. CM Basavaraj Bommai on Monday said that the drive against encroachments in the city will not stop until the last encroachment is cleared and no encroacher, including IT/BT firms, will be spared.

news.title: Form high-power panel to monitor sand mining: NGT to Karnataka government
news.para: The petitioner alleged that miners are carrying out sand mining in waterbodies located in Raichur and Vijayapura districts in the guise of dredging and maintenance of lakes and sought appropriate action from NGT.

news.title: Telangana government to regularise land in Azamabad Industrial Area
news.para: If the plan takes off, state coffers will be replenished with Rs 2,000 crore, while benefiting allottees and industrialists who lobbied with the government to convert the land into freehold for multipurpose use. Official sources said, the move would also stop unauthorized use of leased industrial land.
